        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(7 comments)\n\nThis is good, but have some concerns with usability by other new types of controllers besides tdjam, for example, the DMN controllers that would be introduced in this release.   I suggest to mark this review as work in progress as it is a very good base, and I can work with Taka and folks to revisit a few things to to incorporate other controllers besides tdjam.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "f896980d2f511d5fc6618787336394c554438edc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 743,
          "name": "Ralph Straubs",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "rs8887@att.com",
          "username": "rs8887"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-07-16 08:09:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> (7 comments)\n> \n> This is good, but have some concerns with usability by other new types of controllers besides tdjam, for example, the DMN controllers that would be introduced in this release.   I suggest to mark this review as work in progress as it is a very good base, and I can work with Taka and folks to revisit a few things to to incorporate other controllers besides tdjam.\n\nThere is nothing here specific to tdjam other than the 'AggregatedPolicyController' changes to make some instance variables accessible to subclasses. The other changes just give the flexibility to build alternate 'PolicyController' and 'DroolsController' types.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
